The '''Dame Myra Hess Award''' is an award for postgraduate students of the [[piano]]. It has been presented by the Musicians Benevolent Fund (now [[Help Musicians UK]]) since 1968.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalgallery.org.uk/about-us/press-and-media/press-releases/dame-myra-hess-day-at-the-national-gallery |title=Dame Myra Hess Day at the National Gallery |accessdate=22 March 2016 }}</ref> [[Myra Hess]] had given the MBF crucial financial support during World War II through funds she had raised during her concert series at London's [[National Gallery]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.helpmusicians.org.uk/about-us/history |title=Help Musicians UK: History |accessdate=22 March 2016 }}</ref>

