[[File:SoC Logo 2008.jpg|thumb|right|Stories of Change]] '''''Stories of Change''''' is a 2008 documentary film by [[Kamar Ahmad Simon]].
The documentary focuses on the lives of five women aging from 16 to 60, coming from different walks of life, from different professions, religions and regions of [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sarwat |first=Nadia |date=16 March 2008 |title=Stories of Change: Women tracing a path to live their dreams |url=http://archive.thedailystar.net/newDesign/story.php?nid=27847 |newspaper=The Daily Star}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Ahmad |first=Turaj |date=21 March 2008 |title=Stories of change |url=http://www.newagebd.com/2008/mar/21/mar21/xtra_also1.html |newspaper=New Age |location=Dhaka |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080724230340/http://www.newagebd.com/2008/mar/21/mar21/xtra_also1.html |archive-date=24 July 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title='Stories of Change': Women as agents of social transformation |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-45558 |newspaper=The Daily Star |date=14 July 2008}}</ref>
The film screened at various film festivals:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.storiesofchange.net/html/festivals.htm |title=Festivals |website=Stories of Change, a documentary by Simon & Sara |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120213104844/http://www.storiesofchange.net/html/festivals.htm |archive-date=13 February 2012}}</ref> * Jeevika: [[South Asia Livelihood Documentary Festival]], Delhi (August 28–31, 2008)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jeevika.org/synopsis.htm#storiesofchange/ |title=Synopses of Short listed Films 2008 |website=Jeevika 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090226214935/http://www.jeevika.org/synopsis.htm#storiesofchange/ |archive-date=26 February 2009}}</ref> * [[Asiatica Film Mediale]], Rome (November 15–23, 2008)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/en_schedafilm_view.php?id_config=1&id_scheda=29 |title=Stories Of Change |website=Asiatica Film Mediale |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211235426/http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/en_schedafilm_view.php?id_config=1&id_scheda=29 |archive-date=11 February 2012}} </ref> * [[Goan Peoples' Film Festival]]: Celebrating Life and Livelihoods (November 21–29, 2008) * [[Kolkata International Documentary Film Festival]] (January 26–30, 2009)<ref>{{cite news |title=Docu film festival kicks off |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArchiveView.asp?Daily=TOIKM&AppName=1&login=default&Enter=true&Skin=TOI&GZ=T&BaseHref=TOIKM%2F2009%2F01%2F28&AW=1233134439046&Page=5 |newspaper=Times of India |date=28 January 2009}}</ref>
